§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $X$ is a set. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬discrete metric❭ on $X$ is the function $d: X × X →
    𝗥_+$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ d(x, y) = \begin{cases} ⦉

      ‖ 1 & \text{ if } x = y \\ ⦉

      ‖ 0 & \text{ otherwise } ⦉

      ‖ \end{cases} ⦉
    ⦉⦉
  ‖ In this case, $(X, d)$ is called a ❬discrete metric space❭. ⦉
⦉

